1
00:00:03,721 --> 00:00:06,601
NARRATOR: A long time ago,
on the battlefields of Britain,

2
00:00:06,681 --> 00:00:11,081
an army of enemies came together
to face an impossible opponent

3
00:00:11,801 --> 00:00:13,881
beyond their wildest nightmares.

4
00:00:14,961 --> 00:00:16,521
(ALL SHOUTING)

5
00:00:19,961 --> 00:00:23,921
This unlikely army fought and won
the bloodiest of battles.

6
00:00:26,241 --> 00:00:27,961
But only just.

7
00:00:28,481 --> 00:00:30,881
Their opponent had been so remorseless,

8
00:00:31,241 --> 00:00:33,961
the fear it placed in them was absolute.

9
00:00:34,721 --> 00:00:36,081
So they made a pact.

10
00:00:36,921 --> 00:00:40,521
They split their opponent's
vanquished body into three pieces,

11
00:00:43,241 --> 00:00:45,801
to be buried at
opposite ends of the world,

12
00:00:46,201 --> 00:00:50,761
and vowed that the burial sites would be
forever guarded as a precaution.

13
00:00:56,681 --> 00:00:58,921
The three swore an oath of secrecy.

14
00:01:00,081 --> 00:01:03,561
The terrifying opponent
was to be erased from history.

15
00:01:04,601 --> 00:01:08,361
The three Custodians undertook
their long journeys across land and sea,

16
00:01:09,681 --> 00:01:14,081
locating isolated sites and carrying out
their task with monastic dedication.

17
00:01:17,881 --> 00:01:20,481
Passing their duties down
through the generations,

18
00:01:20,561 --> 00:01:22,001
to protect the future,

19
00:01:22,641 --> 00:01:24,601
the Custodians were unyielding.

20
00:01:40,361 --> 00:01:41,401
(YELPS)

21
00:01:43,121 --> 00:01:46,321
All except one,
whose journey was never made.

22
00:01:46,801 --> 00:01:49,281
Felled at the first
by an unwitting assailant

23
00:01:49,761 --> 00:01:52,161
who would never know
the full impact of his arrow.

24
00:01:55,001 --> 00:01:57,001
And time moved on,

25
00:01:58,721 --> 00:02:01,241
obscuring the lost Custodian's body,

26
00:02:02,081 --> 00:02:06,041
leaving the other two Custodians
and their descendants

27
00:02:06,481 --> 00:02:10,041
unaware of their comrade's fate
for eternity.

28
00:02:12,361 --> 00:02:13,361
Almost.

29
00:02:15,281 --> 00:02:17,201
MITCH: Right, let's have a look.
Where were we?

30
00:02:17,681 --> 00:02:19,281
Oh, yeah, here we go.

31
00:02:20,161 --> 00:02:22,401
I'm so glad you suggested
coming in today.

32
00:02:23,401 --> 00:02:24,961
LIN: I hate New Year's day.

33
00:02:25,481 --> 00:02:27,921
Everything's closed,
everyone is hung over,

34
00:02:28,201 --> 00:02:29,241
and there's nothing to do.

35
00:02:29,721 --> 00:02:32,561
Also, what is cooler than this?

36
00:02:33,441 --> 00:02:36,201
Never thought I'd be involved in
a proper find,

37
00:02:36,641 --> 00:02:39,081
even if this isn't Alfred the Great.

38
00:02:39,601 --> 00:02:42,841
Eh, they found Richard III
in a car park in Leicester,

39
00:02:43,361 --> 00:02:46,721
no reason we can't find Alfred the Great
under Sheffield Town Hall.

40
00:02:47,161 --> 00:02:48,161
No reason.

41
00:02:48,401 --> 00:02:51,241
Oh, apart from history and geography.

42
00:02:51,961 --> 00:02:53,521
Yeah, I was never very good at those.

43
00:02:53,641 --> 00:02:54,721
(BOTH LAUGH)

44
00:02:58,681 --> 00:02:59,681
(CLEARS THROAT)

45
00:03:00,921 --> 00:03:02,001
So, uh,

46
00:03:05,401 --> 00:03:06,601
are we gonna talk about it?

47
00:03:06,881 --> 00:03:08,521
Talk about what, Mitch?

48
00:03:09,361 --> 00:03:10,361
The kiss,

49
00:03:11,721 --> 00:03:12,721
that happened.

50
00:03:13,001 --> 00:03:15,121
Yeah. Yeah, okay, let's talk about that.

51
00:03:16,361 --> 00:03:18,361
So, was it for you...

52
00:03:18,441 --> 00:03:20,721
(STAMMERS) I'm just checking.
I don't wanna presume.

53
00:03:21,161 --> 00:03:25,161
Like a, "Happy New Year mates”
kiss or...

54
00:03:26,601 --> 00:03:27,601
...not?

55
00:03:27,681 --> 00:03:31,241
Did it feel like
a "Happy New Year mates" kiss?

56
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:32,961
No.

57
00:03:34,641 --> 00:03:38,281
-It was more kissy than that, I'd say.
-(LAUGHS)

58
00:03:38,961 --> 00:03:42,361
Oh, good, yeah.
'Cause it was more than that for me.

59
00:03:43,321 --> 00:03:44,561
-Oh, thank God.
-(BOTH LAUGH)

60
00:03:44,721 --> 00:03:47,081
I mean, great... I mean, amazing...
For me too.

61
00:03:47,201 --> 00:03:50,041
Wow. (STAMMERS) I didn't sleep all night
when I got home, 'cause I was wondering.

62
00:03:50,121 --> 00:03:52,241
Me neither.
That's why I texted you to say come in.

63
00:03:52,641 --> 00:03:54,801
-Oh, really?
-Yes, um...

64
00:03:54,921 --> 00:03:56,761
-(SIGHS)
-You idiot.

65
00:03:58,281 --> 00:04:01,441
So, what do we do now?

66
00:04:02,561 --> 00:04:04,961
I mean,
I'm not suggesting that we... Here.

67
00:04:05,081 --> 00:04:06,401
(BOTH LAUGH)

68
00:04:06,681 --> 00:04:09,921
Finish this,
fix a time to go out properly.

69
00:04:10,641 --> 00:04:11,641
How does that sound?

70
00:04:11,801 --> 00:04:13,521
-That sounds awesome.
-(LAUGHS)

71
00:04:14,881 --> 00:04:16,081
It's my favourite year ever.

72
00:04:16,641 --> 00:04:19,281
Already, one day in. (CHUCKLES)

73
00:04:19,681 --> 00:04:21,041
-Look at this.
-Hmm?

74
00:04:21,641 --> 00:04:25,161
Here, just below this side of the hand.
There's something here.

75
00:04:25,241 --> 00:04:27,521
I just can't figure out what it is.

76
00:04:27,681 --> 00:04:30,801
MITCH: Oh, yeah.
Well, let's record it and bag it up.

77
00:04:32,121 --> 00:04:35,001
Contents recorded, coded and bagged.
Whatever it is.

78
00:04:35,121 --> 00:04:36,121
LIN: Thanks.

79
00:04:37,001 --> 00:04:40,801
You do realise, this means
those drawings could be true.

80
00:04:41,561 --> 00:04:42,841
The battle of Hope Valley.

81
00:04:43,441 --> 00:04:47,041
I know you love those documents
and I know you want them to be true,

82
00:04:47,121 --> 00:04:48,641
but this is more significant than that.

83
00:04:48,721 --> 00:04:49,961
A lot more significant.

84
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:53,721
What if he was part of it, hmm?
He could've fought in it.

85
00:04:53,841 --> 00:04:56,001
He could be the key
to unlocking what it was all about.

86
00:04:56,561 --> 00:04:59,481
Or, he could be
nothing to do with it, whatsoever.

87
00:04:59,601 --> 00:05:01,201
You see, that's the difference
between you and me.

88
00:05:01,281 --> 00:05:02,681
I am glass half full.

89
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:04,361
-LIN: Oh, is that right?
-Hundred percent.

90
00:05:04,441 --> 00:05:07,081
LIN: Oh, yeah, who was it who doubted...

91
00:05:10,161 --> 00:05:11,761
(CRACKLING)

92
00:05:40,401 --> 00:05:42,001
(RUMBLING)

93
00:06:02,281 --> 00:06:03,681
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

94
00:06:03,961 --> 00:06:05,241
DOCTOR: Wait for it, last one.

95
00:06:06,281 --> 00:06:09,001
See? Cosmic fireworks.

96
00:06:18,521 --> 00:06:21,721
Hey, Doc, I've got to hand it to you.

97
00:06:21,841 --> 00:06:25,001
That is the best fireworks display
I've ever seen.

98
00:06:26,601 --> 00:06:27,721
-Didn't I say?
-Yeah.

99
00:06:27,801 --> 00:06:30,801
Nineteen New Year's Eves in a row,
which was your favourite?

100
00:06:31,081 --> 00:06:33,401
-I did love Mesopotamia.
-Ah, the original.

101
00:06:34,121 --> 00:06:37,321
Oh, really. So, Iraq invented New Year.

102
00:06:37,401 --> 00:06:40,521
Sydney, 2000. Watching the fireworks
on top of the Harbour Bridge.

103
00:06:40,601 --> 00:06:42,041
-Until you nearly fell off.
-Yeah.

104
00:06:42,121 --> 00:06:44,881
1801, discovering that dwarf planet
with your Italian man.

105
00:06:44,961 --> 00:06:46,401
Lovely Giuseppe Piazza.

106
00:06:46,681 --> 00:06:48,001
-Hmm.
-(SIGHS)

107
00:06:49,761 --> 00:06:51,081
-Should we do one more?
-Yeah.

108
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:52,361
Make it a round 20?

109
00:06:52,881 --> 00:06:54,921
I'm thinking Quantifier.

110
00:06:55,001 --> 00:06:57,241
Little settlement on the edge of
the known universe

111
00:06:57,321 --> 00:06:59,801
where it's permanently New Year's Eve,
every day.

112
00:07:00,721 --> 00:07:02,201
They've got the best blooms.

113
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:03,961
-(BEEPING)
-(SIGHS)

114
00:07:05,441 --> 00:07:08,161
-YASMIN: Is that important?
-No, not really. It's just Earth.

115
00:07:08,241 --> 00:07:10,921
Leave a little alarm on,
as it's your home. Just in case.

116
00:07:11,521 --> 00:07:13,721
-Oh, that's bad.
-What?

117
00:07:13,801 --> 00:07:15,281
Oh, that's worse, that's...

118
00:07:16,401 --> 00:07:18,161
-Worse than worse.
-Wait, what are you getting?

119
00:07:18,441 --> 00:07:22,521
Something or some things,
non-terrestrial,

120
00:07:23,321 --> 00:07:24,801
are attempting a spacial shift.

121
00:07:24,881 --> 00:07:26,761
I'm homing in
on the convergence pattern.

122
00:07:27,121 --> 00:07:29,241
-Anywhere exciting?
-Sheffield.

123
00:07:35,201 --> 00:07:36,281
What was that?

124
00:07:37,441 --> 00:07:38,881
-Did you see anything?
-No.

125
00:07:40,441 --> 00:07:41,441
Could be a rat.

126
00:07:44,121 --> 00:07:45,441
I think there's something missing.

127
00:07:45,961 --> 00:07:47,401
Must've taken one of the bags.

128
00:07:48,241 --> 00:07:49,801
That's one cheeky rat.

129
00:07:51,121 --> 00:07:52,201
I'll take a look.

130
00:07:58,081 --> 00:07:59,481
(WATER SPLASHING)

131
00:08:06,801 --> 00:08:07,961
(GASPS)

132
00:08:09,201 --> 00:08:10,321
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

133
00:08:12,401 --> 00:08:13,801
(WATER SLOSHING)

134
00:08:49,681 --> 00:08:51,641
Oh, my God.

135
00:08:54,601 --> 00:08:55,881
Oh, what's your name?

136
00:08:56,201 --> 00:08:58,321
Mitch.
You just appeared out of thin air.

137
00:08:58,401 --> 00:08:59,481
(STAMMERS) How did you do that?

138
00:08:59,561 --> 00:09:02,801
I'm the Doctor. These are
my best friends, Ryan, Yaz and Graham.

139
00:09:02,881 --> 00:09:03,961
-Hello.
-All right?

140
00:09:04,121 --> 00:09:05,121
Right, okay.

141
00:09:05,201 --> 00:09:06,761
Spend a lot of time in sewers,
do you, Mitch?

142
00:09:06,841 --> 00:09:09,521
We're excavating an ancient burial site.

143
00:09:09,641 --> 00:09:12,561
-When you say "we"...
-Uh, Lin's through here.

144
00:09:12,721 --> 00:09:14,841
Lin! Where are you?

145
00:09:15,001 --> 00:09:16,121
Ah, there you are.

146
00:09:16,201 --> 00:09:18,281
Uh, these guys just sort of arrived.

147
00:09:18,681 --> 00:09:20,721
-LIN: Hi.
-Seen anything unusual then?

148
00:09:21,161 --> 00:09:24,201
(STAMMERS) Yeah, there's something
on the wall back there.

149
00:09:24,521 --> 00:09:25,761
What sort of something?

150
00:09:34,081 --> 00:09:35,281
It's moved.

151
00:09:35,401 --> 00:09:36,481
What did it look like?

152
00:09:37,001 --> 00:09:39,441
Like a massive sort of squid thing.

153
00:09:42,641 --> 00:09:45,401
-RYAN: Ew, really?
-Doc, are you sure that's safe?

154
00:09:45,561 --> 00:09:48,121
Can you get me something to store
this in, for analysis, please, Mitch?

155
00:09:48,201 --> 00:09:49,321
Yeah.

156
00:09:49,601 --> 00:09:53,401
So, Doc, if it was there
and it's not there now,

157
00:09:53,481 --> 00:09:56,961
I assume it's roaming around here,
in the water.

158
00:09:57,721 --> 00:09:59,681
-Should we be worried?
-Probably.

159
00:10:00,241 --> 00:10:03,761
It looks like it slid down this wall
and into the water.

160
00:10:04,601 --> 00:10:05,601
Where are we exactly?

161
00:10:06,041 --> 00:10:07,601
Underneath Sheffield Town Hall.

162
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,881
And where do these sewers lead?

163
00:10:10,641 --> 00:10:11,841
LIN: All the way under the city.

164
00:10:12,961 --> 00:10:14,121
It can be anywhere.

165
00:10:17,361 --> 00:10:19,041
I want you out of these tunnels
right now.

166
00:10:19,121 --> 00:10:20,761
I'm putting this site under quarantine.

167
00:10:21,001 --> 00:10:22,201
Yaz will escort you.

168
00:10:22,281 --> 00:10:24,281
And if you see any sort of creature,
don't go near it.

169
00:10:24,361 --> 00:10:27,641
Not until we've worked out what it is.
Assume proximity is a risk.

170
00:10:27,721 --> 00:10:29,521
Come on, let's get you out of here.

171
00:10:31,561 --> 00:10:32,681
What about the site?

172
00:10:33,001 --> 00:10:35,201
Look, there are valuable
historical artefacts down here.

173
00:10:35,281 --> 00:10:36,681
We've been working on this for months.

174
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:39,281
We'll make sure it's all kept safe.
I've got your details now,

175
00:10:39,361 --> 00:10:41,281
so we'll let you know
when it's okay to come back down.

176
00:10:44,121 --> 00:10:45,281
DOCTOR: Come on, Yaz.

177
00:10:46,961 --> 00:10:47,961
MITCH: That was weird, right?

178
00:10:48,961 --> 00:10:49,961
Yeah.

179
00:10:50,361 --> 00:10:52,441
I'll call the department tomorrow,
let them know what's happened.

180
00:10:52,521 --> 00:10:53,521
Okay.

181
00:10:53,601 --> 00:10:55,321
I guess we could go for that drink now.

182
00:10:55,521 --> 00:10:56,641
Not right now.

183
00:10:56,841 --> 00:10:58,001
No. Right. Of course.

184
00:10:58,081 --> 00:10:59,721
-I didn't mean to...
-I'm a bit freaked out.

185
00:11:00,401 --> 00:11:01,921
I'll call you if I hear anything
from them.

186
00:11:02,641 --> 00:11:04,481
-Maybe we'll be back in tomorrow.
-Yeah.

187
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,241
(SIGHS)

188
00:11:16,801 --> 00:11:17,921
(MOBILE CHIMES)

189
00:11:19,801 --> 00:11:21,561
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

190
00:11:28,721 --> 00:11:30,521
DOCTOR: I've got the TARDIS
scanning the sewers

191
00:11:30,601 --> 00:11:32,441
for non-terrestrial life signals.

192
00:11:33,241 --> 00:11:34,601
So, where are we actually going?

193
00:11:34,961 --> 00:11:36,841
-Your house, of course.
-What?

194
00:11:37,441 --> 00:11:38,601
-(GRUNTS)
-Whoa!

195
00:11:40,361 --> 00:11:41,361
Oh.

196
00:11:42,921 --> 00:11:45,361
-Whoops.
-GRAHAM: You've landed on my chair.

197
00:11:47,001 --> 00:11:48,641
-Sorry.
-You broke my chair.

198
00:11:48,721 --> 00:11:50,641
Well, if you will leave chairs
around the place...

199
00:11:50,721 --> 00:11:52,921
-This is my front room.
-DOCTOR: Where's your kitchen?

200
00:11:53,121 --> 00:11:55,161
I just need to get some eggs
to check the protein alignments

201
00:11:55,241 --> 00:11:56,361
-in the goo.
-(SIGHS)

202
00:11:56,441 --> 00:11:57,921
-(DOORBELL RINGS)
-Oh!

203
00:11:58,121 --> 00:11:59,761
Is that your intruder alert or mine?

204
00:11:59,841 --> 00:12:01,761
-It's the doorbell.
-Oh, yeah. Sorry.

205
00:12:03,721 --> 00:12:04,761
No.

206
00:12:06,401 --> 00:12:07,561
-Who was it?
-Wrong number.

207
00:12:07,641 --> 00:12:09,841
-(DOORBELL RINGS)
-Intruder alert again?

208
00:12:10,001 --> 00:12:12,321
-GRAHAM: It's a doorbell.
-I'll go tell him to go away.

209
00:12:12,401 --> 00:12:13,561
Oh, Ryan, uh...

210
00:12:14,281 --> 00:12:16,721
-Is everything all right?
-Not really, Yaz, no.

211
00:12:21,881 --> 00:12:23,041
YASMIN: Ryan, are you okay?

212
00:12:25,321 --> 00:12:27,601
This is Yaz, and the Doctor.

213
00:12:28,841 --> 00:12:29,841
Hi.

214
00:12:29,921 --> 00:12:31,321
This is my dad.

215
00:12:31,881 --> 00:12:32,921
BOTH: Oh.

216
00:12:33,121 --> 00:12:34,121
Graham.

217
00:12:35,361 --> 00:12:36,441
Hi, Ryan's dad.

218
00:12:37,801 --> 00:12:39,801
-Aaron.
-You weren't at Grace's funeral.

219
00:12:42,281 --> 00:12:43,801
-No.
-Ryan waited for you.

220
00:12:45,241 --> 00:12:46,241
You let him down.

221
00:12:52,241 --> 00:12:55,321
Uh, I was thinking maybe
if we could grab a coffee...

222
00:12:56,041 --> 00:12:58,081
Um, yeah, right, sure.

223
00:12:58,521 --> 00:13:00,241
Is it all right if we, um...

224
00:13:00,841 --> 00:13:03,401
We're just gonna...
Is that okay if, um...

225
00:13:04,241 --> 00:13:07,281
If you're needing somewhere to go,
café around the corner is open.

226
00:13:07,601 --> 00:13:10,801
Yeah. Yeah, good shout, good shout.
I'll just get my coat.

227
00:13:13,121 --> 00:13:14,961
Aaron, uh, can I have a word?

228
00:13:17,601 --> 00:13:19,281
(SIGHS) Ryan's dad.

229
00:13:21,041 --> 00:13:22,841
-It's complicated.
-Yeah.

230
00:13:23,721 --> 00:13:24,881
Dads are.

231
00:13:25,961 --> 00:13:27,041
So I've heard.

232
00:13:29,001 --> 00:13:30,521
(SIGHS) So,

233
00:13:31,481 --> 00:13:32,681
why are you here?

234
00:13:34,081 --> 00:13:36,401
New Year's Day. Turning over a new leaf.

235
00:13:37,801 --> 00:13:41,681
Right. Well, um, be gentle.
He's been through a lot.

236
00:13:42,121 --> 00:13:45,681
-I know.
-No, you have no idea.

237
00:13:49,001 --> 00:13:52,121
I just wanted me and him
to be a family again.

238
00:13:53,761 --> 00:13:55,641
Family isn't just about DNA, Aaron,

239
00:13:56,801 --> 00:13:57,841
or a name.

240
00:13:59,401 --> 00:14:00,681
It's about what you do.

241
00:14:01,201 --> 00:14:03,161
And you haven't done enough.

242
00:14:03,401 --> 00:14:04,881
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

243
00:14:05,401 --> 00:14:06,401
Are we off then?

244
00:14:10,281 --> 00:14:12,161
-See you later, Gramps.
-(CHUCKLES)

245
00:14:12,361 --> 00:14:13,361
"Gramps"?

246
00:14:17,801 --> 00:14:19,201
-See you later, son.
-(DOOR OPENS)

247
00:14:20,321 --> 00:14:21,361
(CHUCKLES)

248
00:14:29,241 --> 00:14:30,321
(GROANS)

249
00:14:31,481 --> 00:14:33,121
WOMAN: Lin, is that you?

250
00:14:33,801 --> 00:14:34,921
(CHOKES) Yep.

251
00:14:35,321 --> 00:14:37,401
WOMAN: I'm making breakfast.
You want some?

252
00:14:38,241 --> 00:14:39,841
I'm just gonna have a shower.

253
00:14:40,401 --> 00:14:42,881
WOMAN: Did you see Mitch? How did it go?

254
00:14:43,921 --> 00:14:45,881
(PANTING)

255
00:14:52,121 --> 00:14:53,921
(PANTING)

256
00:15:06,881 --> 00:15:08,081
CREATURE: No!

257
00:15:08,281 --> 00:15:09,521
(PANTING) Who are...

258
00:15:10,441 --> 00:15:11,681
What are you?

259
00:15:11,761 --> 00:15:15,321
CREATURE: I am your pilot now.

260
00:15:16,721 --> 00:15:18,401
Do not fight me.

261
00:15:18,601 --> 00:15:20,921
I have control over your body.

262
00:15:21,121 --> 00:15:25,121
All brain and motor functions
are under my power.

263
00:15:25,201 --> 00:15:26,921
Please, no...

264
00:15:27,001 --> 00:15:28,281
-Silence.
-(GASPS)

265
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:30,401
See how I control you.

266
00:15:30,601 --> 00:15:32,281
Turn.

267
00:15:32,521 --> 00:15:33,561
Look.

268
00:15:35,801 --> 00:15:37,761
(GROANING)

269
00:15:41,481 --> 00:15:44,441
BOTH: You are my prisoner now.

270
00:15:46,761 --> 00:15:48,041
(PANTING)

271
00:15:48,121 --> 00:15:51,761
You are my puppet.

272
00:15:52,601 --> 00:15:55,161
(LAUGHS)

273
00:15:58,321 --> 00:16:00,161
DOCTOR: Bio-profiling nearly complete.

274
00:16:00,321 --> 00:16:02,801
-(CONSOLE SOUNDS)
-Yes, a match.

275
00:16:03,601 --> 00:16:04,881
Let's see what we've got.

276
00:16:08,161 --> 00:16:09,161
No.

277
00:16:10,001 --> 00:16:11,321
It can't be.

278
00:16:11,401 --> 00:16:14,161
Doctor, I don't like it
when you go quiet.

279
00:16:18,001 --> 00:16:21,001
This is the DNA of the most
dangerous creature in the universe.

280
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:22,681
Does it have a name?

281
00:16:24,721 --> 00:16:26,281
The Dalek.

282
00:16:29,361 --> 00:16:30,521
DALEK: Cover me.

283
00:16:33,041 --> 00:16:34,081
Sit.

284
00:16:35,841 --> 00:16:37,921
Now, open the machine.

285
00:16:39,921 --> 00:16:43,961
I must know everything
of this planet's capability.

286
00:16:44,201 --> 00:16:48,041
Its systems, its weapons and its armies.

287
00:16:48,201 --> 00:16:51,281
Everything that must be destroyed.

288
00:16:52,641 --> 00:16:55,841
No, I won't do this.

289
00:16:55,921 --> 00:16:57,201
You have no choice.

290
00:16:57,281 --> 00:17:01,361
Do not struggle or your friends will die

291
00:17:01,561 --> 00:17:03,521
at your hands.

292
00:17:04,601 --> 00:17:06,161
(GASPING) What do you want?

293
00:17:06,641 --> 00:17:10,601
To fulfil my purpose at last.

294
00:17:11,081 --> 00:17:14,241
The Dalek is a mutated remnant
of a warring race.

295
00:17:14,721 --> 00:17:18,081
Genetically created
and housed within a metal case,

296
00:17:18,241 --> 00:17:20,481
designed to be
a relentless killing machine.

297
00:17:20,721 --> 00:17:23,121
Lin said she saw a creature
that looked more like a squid.

298
00:17:23,281 --> 00:17:24,761
It sounds as though
the internal creature

299
00:17:24,841 --> 00:17:26,441
has become separated from its casing.

300
00:17:26,521 --> 00:17:28,161
Well, then, it's vulnerable.

301
00:17:28,561 --> 00:17:32,121
Oh, come on, Doc. Look, one squid
versus seven billion humans and you.

302
00:17:32,201 --> 00:17:34,081
Odds have got to be
in our favour, surely.

303
00:17:36,001 --> 00:17:37,681
I always think I'm rid of them.

304
00:17:38,721 --> 00:17:39,721
Never am.

305
00:17:40,561 --> 00:17:43,201
Trust me, Graham,
even if it's just one, it's enough.

306
00:17:43,721 --> 00:17:46,121
It's gonna kill anyone
that gets in its path,

307
00:17:46,201 --> 00:17:49,241
and it's not gonna stop
until it's taken control of this planet.

308
00:17:49,521 --> 00:17:51,441
There's an alien on the loose
in an archaeological dig.

309
00:17:51,521 --> 00:17:53,721
-Is that where it started?
-I don't know.

310
00:17:53,801 --> 00:17:56,001
-LIN: Hi, this...
-(SIGHS) Voicemail.

311
00:17:56,961 --> 00:17:59,481
Lin, hi, it's Yasmin Khan.

312
00:18:00,161 --> 00:18:02,241
We met in the sewers earlier.

313
00:18:02,561 --> 00:18:03,801
Can you give me a call?

314
00:18:03,881 --> 00:18:07,081
Out of its shell. It can't have got far.

315
00:18:08,521 --> 00:18:10,081
But how's it getting about?

316
00:18:11,121 --> 00:18:12,681
(TYRES SCREECHING)

317
00:18:15,681 --> 00:18:17,241
(CAR HORN HONKING)

318
00:18:17,561 --> 00:18:18,961
DALEK: Faster.

319
00:18:25,761 --> 00:18:29,681
Increase speed.
Nothing shall halt the mission.

320
00:18:31,161 --> 00:18:33,441
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

321
00:18:34,361 --> 00:18:37,041
I sense your thoughts.

322
00:18:37,521 --> 00:18:40,001
That sound is no rescue.

323
00:18:41,121 --> 00:18:43,521
It ls combat.

324
00:18:57,481 --> 00:18:59,641
Can you wind your window down
for me, please, love?

325
00:19:03,841 --> 00:19:05,361
Do you know what speed
you were doing, love?

326
00:19:06,081 --> 00:19:08,041
103 miles per hour.

327
00:19:09,601 --> 00:19:10,961
What have you got to say about that?

328
00:19:12,121 --> 00:19:15,081
You are an enemy of the Daleks.

329
00:19:15,961 --> 00:19:17,281
I'm what, sorry?

330
00:19:18,001 --> 00:19:20,841
You are an enemy of the Daleks.

331
00:19:21,841 --> 00:19:23,121
(POLICEMAN SIGHS)

332
00:19:24,921 --> 00:19:26,761
And how are you spelling that? (SIGHS)

333
00:19:29,921 --> 00:19:30,921
(GASPS)

334
00:19:36,001 --> 00:19:37,161
Flipping hell.

335
00:19:50,201 --> 00:19:51,201
(SCREAMS)

336
00:19:52,841 --> 00:19:54,641
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

337
00:19:58,361 --> 00:20:01,921
You are a useful soldier.

338
00:20:04,961 --> 00:20:06,361
AARON: But this one's a combination.

339
00:20:06,601 --> 00:20:08,401
Microwave and full oven.

340
00:20:08,561 --> 00:20:10,641
Both functions are the best quality
you can get.

341
00:20:10,721 --> 00:20:12,521
I swear, this is the best you can have.

342
00:20:12,601 --> 00:20:14,801
Uh, sorry, not for me, mate.

343
00:20:25,321 --> 00:20:27,561
-(EXHALES)
-This is a new thing you're doing?

344
00:20:29,161 --> 00:20:31,201
Only so long a man can work offshore.

345
00:20:32,241 --> 00:20:33,521
Given up being on the rigs?

346
00:20:35,121 --> 00:20:39,801
Let's just say, I've been examining
my life choices lately.

347
00:20:42,361 --> 00:20:44,041
Not sure if this is the answer.

348
00:20:45,401 --> 00:20:46,561
Get them online, can't you?

349
00:20:49,161 --> 00:20:50,561
Yep. Yes.

350
00:20:51,321 --> 00:20:54,281
Yes, except for this one.

351
00:20:55,521 --> 00:20:57,161
It's actually really good.

352
00:20:58,201 --> 00:21:00,561
A mate of mine makes it.
I helped him with some of the specs.

353
00:21:00,681 --> 00:21:02,961
It's the best working oven you can get.

354
00:21:03,921 --> 00:21:05,961
(LAUGHS) But I make it sound like a con.

355
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:10,081
So, maybe I'm not cut out for that.

356
00:21:10,961 --> 00:21:14,681
Maybe it's back to engineering.

357
00:21:15,321 --> 00:21:16,361
We'll see.

358
00:21:17,521 --> 00:21:19,921
So, how you been doing?

359
00:21:20,761 --> 00:21:22,121
Seriously?

360
00:21:22,201 --> 00:21:24,081
-That's where you start?
-What?

361
00:21:24,161 --> 00:21:26,641
That's all you got?
How do you think I'm doing?

362
00:21:28,081 --> 00:21:31,121
-I know it's been hard for both of us...
-Okay, stop.

363
00:21:32,401 --> 00:21:33,761
I don't care how it's been for you.

364
00:21:34,441 --> 00:21:36,961
This ain't about us
commiserating with each other.

365
00:21:37,321 --> 00:21:39,441
This is about you making things right.

366
00:21:40,401 --> 00:21:41,601
This is how you talk to your dad?

367
00:21:41,681 --> 00:21:43,081
I don't know,
"cause he ain't been around.

368
00:21:44,321 --> 00:21:48,161
So, don't come walking back in,
demanding respect,

369
00:21:48,641 --> 00:21:50,281
"cause that ain't where we are.

370
00:21:58,081 --> 00:21:59,441
What do you need me to say?

371
00:22:00,761 --> 00:22:01,801
Hmm?

372
00:22:03,041 --> 00:22:04,481
'Cause I wanna say it.

373
00:22:09,561 --> 00:22:10,561
Okay.

374
00:22:11,881 --> 00:22:12,881
You say,

375
00:22:14,281 --> 00:22:17,761
"Ryan, I'm sorry,

376
00:22:21,321 --> 00:22:22,321
"I've messed up.

377
00:22:24,161 --> 00:22:25,361
"I haven't been good enough.

378
00:22:27,561 --> 00:22:29,921
"I've let you down a lot.

379
00:22:32,321 --> 00:22:34,681
"And I know this made life hard for you.

380
00:22:36,801 --> 00:22:38,401
"And if it meant

381
00:22:40,001 --> 00:22:44,121
"that over the years,
you've ever felt lonely or abandoned,

382
00:22:44,761 --> 00:22:48,161
"or didn't know where to turn,
or who to talk to,

383
00:22:48,321 --> 00:22:49,721
"or how to be,

384
00:22:50,801 --> 00:22:52,401
"then, I'm sorry.

385
00:22:53,921 --> 00:22:54,921
"'Cause...

386
00:22:55,921 --> 00:22:59,281
"'Cause you mustn't ever think
that you didn't deserve my love."”

387
00:23:01,801 --> 00:23:03,601
-You didn't ever think that.
-(SCOFFS)

388
00:23:07,041 --> 00:23:08,081
Yeah.

389
00:23:10,841 --> 00:23:11,841
Why wouldn't you?

390
00:23:18,441 --> 00:23:20,801
Okay. Listen.

391
00:23:25,961 --> 00:23:28,841
Here's what you find out
when you get older.

392
00:23:32,121 --> 00:23:33,881
There are things you've done
in your life

393
00:23:36,601 --> 00:23:37,681
to others,

394
00:23:39,441 --> 00:23:40,841
the decisions you've made,

395
00:23:43,681 --> 00:23:44,721
maybe when

396
00:23:47,921 --> 00:23:49,241
things were difficult.

397
00:23:50,801 --> 00:23:52,041
You get it wrong.

398
00:23:54,281 --> 00:23:56,321
But by the time you realise
you got it wrong,

399
00:23:57,881 --> 00:23:59,041
it's too late.

400
00:24:00,601 --> 00:24:03,041
You can't fix it
because the damage is done.

401
00:24:07,721 --> 00:24:08,961
And so you run,

402
00:24:11,161 --> 00:24:12,681
'cause you're too ashamed

403
00:24:14,841 --> 00:24:16,081
to make it right.

404
00:24:22,281 --> 00:24:23,521
That's what I did.

405
00:24:25,601 --> 00:24:26,641
No.

406
00:24:27,961 --> 00:24:29,441
You hid when I needed you.

407
00:24:30,881 --> 00:24:33,681
First Mum, then Nan.

408
00:24:43,401 --> 00:24:44,841
I'm not hiding any more.

409
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:50,921
We reckon ninth or tenth century.

410
00:24:51,161 --> 00:24:54,281
Part of our funding came from a group
who think it could be Alfred the Great.

411
00:24:54,761 --> 00:24:57,081
YASMIN: Mitch? Are you there?

412
00:25:00,041 --> 00:25:01,881
-There you are.
-But I'm on the phone to you.

413
00:25:01,961 --> 00:25:04,521
-We followed your signal.
-DOCTOR: Have you got him? Come on.

414
00:25:04,601 --> 00:25:05,721
How does it do that?

415
00:25:05,801 --> 00:25:07,601
Oh, it's even better than that.

416
00:25:08,241 --> 00:25:09,361
Deep breath, Mitch.

417
00:25:11,881 --> 00:25:13,321
Welcome to the TARDIS.

418
00:25:16,081 --> 00:25:17,521
(RUMBLES)

419
00:25:17,841 --> 00:25:19,241
DOCTOR: Now we've got the DNA,

420
00:25:19,321 --> 00:25:20,721
maybe I can rig up the TARDIS

421
00:25:20,801 --> 00:25:24,521
to scan for any other traces
in this tiny corner of space and time.

422
00:25:24,601 --> 00:25:25,721
MITCH: No way.

423
00:25:26,321 --> 00:25:28,961
The internal dimensions are bigger than
the box's external dimensions.

424
00:25:29,041 --> 00:25:31,401
-No biggie.
-No, that is quite a biggie.

425
00:25:31,481 --> 00:25:32,561
Got time over.

426
00:25:32,681 --> 00:25:35,001
Was there anything alien-looking
that you uncovered?

427
00:25:35,401 --> 00:25:38,201
What? No. They're historical artefacts,
they've been there for centuries.

428
00:25:40,001 --> 00:25:43,081
Wait. You're not from
the Order of the Custodians?

429
00:25:43,161 --> 00:25:44,641
What's the Order of the Custodians?

430
00:25:45,361 --> 00:25:47,841
So, these guys reckon
there was a battle.

431
00:25:48,601 --> 00:25:49,921
This mythic creature was killed

432
00:25:50,001 --> 00:25:52,081
and it was split and buried
all over the world.

433
00:25:53,441 --> 00:25:55,161
The spacial shift we detected,

434
00:25:55,241 --> 00:25:57,881
parts of the creature
coming back together.

435
00:25:58,801 --> 00:26:00,481
Oh, don't tell me.

436
00:26:01,321 --> 00:26:02,361
When you uncover something,

437
00:26:02,441 --> 00:26:04,321
you leave it under
the ultraviolet lights

438
00:26:04,401 --> 00:26:06,401
-you had in the sewers.
-Yeah.

439
00:26:06,761 --> 00:26:09,921
Ultraviolet light activates
the dormant creature,

440
00:26:10,201 --> 00:26:11,641
bringing it back to life.

441
00:26:11,881 --> 00:26:13,321
Did you say ninth century?

442
00:26:13,561 --> 00:26:14,561
Yeah.

443
00:26:19,241 --> 00:26:22,961
There's been a Dalek buried on Earth
since the ninth century,

444
00:26:24,481 --> 00:26:25,921
waiting to revive.

445
00:26:26,521 --> 00:26:27,721
I'm sorry, a what?

446
00:26:28,201 --> 00:26:29,561
Alien psychopath.

447
00:26:30,441 --> 00:26:31,681
-Are you kidding?
-No.

448
00:26:31,761 --> 00:26:32,961
But where is it?

449
00:26:33,321 --> 00:26:35,001
How is it getting about? Come on, think.

450
00:26:35,081 --> 00:26:36,281
Have you told Lin?

451
00:26:36,481 --> 00:26:39,841
I tried. Phone's going to voicemail
and she's not replying to texts.

452
00:26:39,961 --> 00:26:42,081
What? No,
she keeps her phone on all the time.

453
00:26:42,161 --> 00:26:44,721
It's a running joke between us.
She's the instant replier.

454
00:26:45,801 --> 00:26:47,641
In the sewers,
were you together all the time?

455
00:26:47,801 --> 00:26:49,281
No, she went off to look for...

456
00:26:49,961 --> 00:26:51,281
one of the missing artefacts.

457
00:26:51,641 --> 00:26:52,921
That's when she found the squid.

458
00:26:53,401 --> 00:26:54,561
Tell me she's safe.

459
00:26:55,281 --> 00:26:56,281
I can't.

460
00:27:03,121 --> 00:27:04,561
MITCH: Where are you going?
What are you doing?

461
00:27:04,641 --> 00:27:06,161
GRAHAM: Just follow and do
what she says, Mitch.

462
00:27:06,241 --> 00:27:08,841
DOCTOR: Lin's number is in Yaz's phone.
If I can connect it to the TARDIS,

463
00:27:08,921 --> 00:27:10,281
-we can locate her.
-(CONSOLE BEEPS)

464
00:27:12,601 --> 00:27:13,801
Getting something.

465
00:27:14,001 --> 00:27:15,801
No, lost it.

466
00:27:16,041 --> 00:27:17,761
-(CONSOLE WHIRS AND BEEPS)
-Yeah!

467
00:27:19,081 --> 00:27:21,441
Bio-fix on the location
of the Dalek DNA.

468
00:27:22,001 --> 00:27:23,121
Right.

469
00:27:24,001 --> 00:27:25,841
(PANTING) Cross-reference

470
00:27:26,361 --> 00:27:28,721
with the signal triangulation
of Lin's phone.

471
00:27:29,921 --> 00:27:31,281
(BEEPING)

472
00:27:31,481 --> 00:27:32,601
It's the same place.

473
00:27:33,761 --> 00:27:35,441
Lin and that creature, they're together.

474
00:27:36,041 --> 00:27:37,561
You mean he's holding her hostage?

475
00:27:37,761 --> 00:27:39,921
I'm really sorry, Mitch.
I think it's crueller than that.

476
00:27:40,001 --> 00:27:41,721
I think it's using her to move about.

477
00:27:42,801 --> 00:27:44,001
MITCH: How can you be so sure?

478
00:27:44,281 --> 00:27:46,601
I learned to think like a Dalek
a long time ago.

479
00:27:47,921 --> 00:27:49,761
Hello? The door's...

480
00:27:51,481 --> 00:27:53,641
I need to use the... You know.

481
00:27:54,081 --> 00:27:56,001
Dad, you know you can say "toilet,"
you know.

482
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:59,201
MITCH: Can you get to Lin?
You have to help her.

483
00:27:59,281 --> 00:28:00,961
-How'd it go with your dad?
-Don't ask.

484
00:28:01,321 --> 00:28:03,761
I don't want him here.
Take this, will you?

485
00:28:03,841 --> 00:28:05,441
You can't just leave him outside,
can you?

486
00:28:05,641 --> 00:28:06,841
(BEEPS LOUDLY)

487
00:28:07,841 --> 00:28:09,201
-(SCREAMS)
-YASMIN: What just happened?

488
00:28:10,001 --> 00:28:11,841
DOCTOR: It can't do that.
How did it do that?

489
00:28:12,761 --> 00:28:14,161
It's blown the systems.

490
00:28:15,921 --> 00:28:17,321
Shorted the navigation.

491
00:28:18,201 --> 00:28:20,841
Fold-back blast
from the creature itself.

492
00:28:21,561 --> 00:28:22,881
It can't do that.

493
00:28:23,401 --> 00:28:24,441
Unless,

494
00:28:25,721 --> 00:28:28,601
-it's a reconnaissance scout.
-In English.

495
00:28:30,921 --> 00:28:34,361
Recon scouts have capabilities
beyond the normal Dalek soldier.

496
00:28:34,961 --> 00:28:37,561
Specially advanced from the basic Dalek.

497
00:28:37,641 --> 00:28:39,281
The first to leave Skaro.

498
00:28:40,321 --> 00:28:42,121
Possibly the first to reach Earth.

499
00:28:42,401 --> 00:28:45,521
So, it's even worse
than the really bad thing

500
00:28:45,601 --> 00:28:47,001
you was worried about
in the first place.

501
00:28:48,241 --> 00:28:50,921
-Graham, emergency peanut-butter run.
-What?

502
00:28:51,161 --> 00:28:53,201
I need to grease
the geo-feudal locks, quick.

503
00:28:53,281 --> 00:28:55,681
-Chop-chop, Grandad.
-Oh, I'm just a gofer.

504
00:28:56,521 --> 00:28:58,481
I'm not having this.

505
00:29:14,001 --> 00:29:16,961
Whoa! You gave me a fright.

506
00:29:17,121 --> 00:29:20,281
-I wasn't expecting... It's just...
-Who has access to the archives?

507
00:29:21,521 --> 00:29:23,401
Today, it's just me. Hello.

508
00:29:23,961 --> 00:29:25,601
Most secure digits in Yorkshire.

509
00:29:25,681 --> 00:29:27,281
That's what I tell me
boyfriend, anyway.

510
00:29:29,001 --> 00:29:30,801
I probably shouldn't be
telling you that.

511
00:29:32,121 --> 00:29:33,361
I'm new at this.

512
00:29:34,201 --> 00:29:35,201
Why?

513
00:29:45,321 --> 00:29:46,601
-(PANEL BEEPING)
-(DOOR OPENS)

514
00:30:25,761 --> 00:30:28,881
DALEK:
I will destroy the energy signal...

515
00:30:28,961 --> 00:30:31,521
DOCTOR: Stop. I know you can hear me
right now.

516
00:30:33,201 --> 00:30:35,601
Who are you?

517
00:30:36,121 --> 00:30:38,001
I'm your secret conscience.

518
00:30:38,841 --> 00:30:40,601
Not really.
We both know you don't have one.

519
00:30:41,401 --> 00:30:43,001
How are you communicating?

520
00:30:43,121 --> 00:30:45,321
You might have temporarily disabled
my navigation,

521
00:30:45,401 --> 00:30:46,801
but I still know a trick or two.

522
00:30:46,881 --> 00:30:49,601
Like I know you're a refugee
from the planet Skaro.

523
00:30:50,641 --> 00:30:52,161
What sort of Dalek are you, anyway?

524
00:30:53,121 --> 00:30:55,801
My mission is
reconnaissance and conquest.

525
00:30:56,201 --> 00:30:58,641
Just as I thought. Recon scout.

526
00:30:58,961 --> 00:31:02,121
All humanity is my prisoner now.

527
00:31:02,401 --> 00:31:03,521
In your dreams, mate.

528
00:31:03,601 --> 00:31:06,801
You've got no casing, no weapons
and no chance.

529
00:31:07,001 --> 00:31:09,281
I have weapons.

530
00:31:10,761 --> 00:31:11,841
Right.

531
00:31:12,001 --> 00:31:15,001
Okay, well, whoop-de-doo.

532
00:31:15,401 --> 00:31:18,081
You've got a weapon after all.
Lot of good it's gonna do you.

533
00:31:18,521 --> 00:31:22,681
DALEX: This planet is now
the property of the Daleks.

534
00:31:22,801 --> 00:31:25,641
I know seven billion people who may have
something to say about that.

535
00:31:26,121 --> 00:31:28,041
Now, you might have a weapon,

536
00:31:28,481 --> 00:31:30,201
but you're a long way from conquest.

537
00:31:30,521 --> 00:31:32,161
Release the woman
you're holding prisoner.

538
00:31:33,201 --> 00:31:35,081
(DALEK LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

539
00:31:40,641 --> 00:31:42,801
-What's it doing?
-I think it's laughing.

540
00:31:44,561 --> 00:31:46,281
(WHIRRING)

541
00:31:50,041 --> 00:31:52,481
Now, do that again to my face.

542
00:31:52,681 --> 00:31:55,041
What is this?

543
00:31:55,441 --> 00:31:59,401
These are my serious tech skillz.
And yes, that is with a "Z."

544
00:32:00,041 --> 00:32:02,841
Bio-tracking fuse to hold projection.

545
00:32:03,041 --> 00:32:07,001
Won't last long, but I need you to see
just how serious my face is right now.

546
00:32:07,521 --> 00:32:09,201
But it's not just you I want to talk to.

547
00:32:10,561 --> 00:32:12,561
-(LIN GROANS)
-Lin, I know you can hear me.

548
00:32:12,641 --> 00:32:16,041
I need you to know we're coming for you.
So keep fighting.

549
00:32:16,761 --> 00:32:18,441
-Mitch is here with us.
-I'm not leaving you.

550
00:32:18,721 --> 00:32:21,321
-(GASPING)
-I know you're scared. Keep fighting.

551
00:32:22,361 --> 00:32:23,641
(GROANS)

552
00:32:24,601 --> 00:32:28,001
This feeble vessel will not fight.

553
00:32:28,761 --> 00:32:31,601
The Daleks are supreme.

554
00:32:32,441 --> 00:32:34,041
(TARDIS BEEPS)

555
00:32:34,121 --> 00:32:36,041
Yeah? If you're so supreme,

556
00:32:36,601 --> 00:32:39,361
how come you let me keep you chatting
while I rebooted my systems?

557
00:32:40,841 --> 00:32:44,481
Here's my New Year's resolution,
I'm coming for you, Dalek.

558
00:32:44,561 --> 00:32:46,201
Lin, hold on.

559
00:32:46,281 --> 00:32:48,481
Blocking signal... (GROANS)

560
00:32:52,201 --> 00:32:53,641
Not getting away from me now.

561
00:32:55,361 --> 00:32:56,801
(TYRES SCREECH)

562
00:33:02,761 --> 00:33:03,761
Where'd they go?

563
00:33:05,001 --> 00:33:06,601
AARON: Did they take the cabinet?

564
00:33:07,321 --> 00:33:08,441
They've gone without me.

565
00:33:08,921 --> 00:33:11,321
(MITCH PANTING)

566
00:33:12,961 --> 00:33:15,441
MDZ Research. What was it doing there?

567
00:33:15,521 --> 00:33:17,641
Uh, they're a weapons research company.

568
00:33:17,961 --> 00:33:19,921
The Order of the Custodians
claim that MDZ were buying up

569
00:33:20,001 --> 00:33:21,881
any non-terrestrial weaponry
on the black market.

570
00:33:21,961 --> 00:33:23,321
What do you think it got there?

571
00:33:24,281 --> 00:33:26,321
-DOCTOR: I don't know.
-(CONSOLE WHIRRING)

572
00:33:27,121 --> 00:33:29,841
Oh, it's blocking the bio-fix now.

573
00:33:30,961 --> 00:33:32,521
-(CONSOLE BEEPING)
-I'm going old-school.

574
00:33:34,041 --> 00:33:37,521
Tracking CCTV cameras, GPS
and number plate tracking.

575
00:33:43,361 --> 00:33:45,601
It's shooting out the cameras
to stop us tracking it.

576
00:33:46,201 --> 00:33:48,921
(GRUNTS) It's taken out
the whole junction box.

577
00:33:49,001 --> 00:33:51,361
Right. Switching to
satellite monitoring.

578
00:33:51,561 --> 00:33:53,361
See, it can't get away that easy.

579
00:33:54,321 --> 00:33:56,401
Where's it going? What's it doing?

580
00:33:56,481 --> 00:33:58,241
If I knew that,
I wouldn't be this panicked.

581
00:33:59,121 --> 00:34:01,561
- (CRACKLES)
-We're gonna need some help.

582
00:34:08,561 --> 00:34:11,281
UK security helpline, this is Polly.
How can I help?

583
00:34:11,881 --> 00:34:14,481
-I'm sorry, what?
-UK security helpline.

584
00:34:14,561 --> 00:34:15,801
How can I help?

585
00:34:16,081 --> 00:34:18,841
Get me Kate Stewart at UNIT.

586
00:34:18,921 --> 00:34:20,881
This is a code zero emergency.

587
00:34:21,121 --> 00:34:22,881
I don't know what that is, I'm afraid.

588
00:34:23,001 --> 00:34:24,761
Which organisation did you say?

589
00:34:25,641 --> 00:34:30,121
UNIT. Unified Intelligence Taskforce.

590
00:34:30,841 --> 00:34:32,281
This is incredibly urgent.

591
00:34:32,481 --> 00:34:35,281
The fate of the entire planet
is at stake.

592
00:34:36,601 --> 00:34:39,121
-I'm checking for you.
-(SIGHS)

593
00:34:41,001 --> 00:34:45,441
Oh, I'm so sorry. UNIT operations
have been suspended, pending review.

594
00:34:45,601 --> 00:34:47,841
What? No, it can't have been.

595
00:34:48,281 --> 00:34:52,801
UNIT is a fundamentally vital protection
for planet Earth against alien invasion.

596
00:34:52,961 --> 00:34:54,361
Yes, but when did that last happen?

597
00:34:54,441 --> 00:34:56,081
Now! Right now!

598
00:34:56,401 --> 00:34:57,401
What happened to it?

599
00:34:58,201 --> 00:34:59,561
I'm just checking.

600
00:35:00,241 --> 00:35:03,921
All UNIT operations were put on hold
following financial disputes,

601
00:35:04,001 --> 00:35:08,201
and subsequent funding withdrawal by
the UK's major international partners.

602
00:35:09,761 --> 00:35:10,761
You're kidding.

603
00:35:11,201 --> 00:35:14,361
Other armed forces are available
if you can answer a couple of questions

604
00:35:14,481 --> 00:35:15,921
-to help me best direct your call.
-(MOBILE BEEPS)

605
00:35:22,281 --> 00:35:23,281
We're on our own.

606
00:35:24,681 --> 00:35:25,721
(ALL SIGH)

607
00:35:27,601 --> 00:35:28,841
Since you're here...

608
00:35:29,081 --> 00:35:30,921
-What's this?
-Have a look.

609
00:35:35,241 --> 00:35:36,601
When my mum died,

610
00:35:37,361 --> 00:35:39,801
my dad got rid of all her things
super quick.

611
00:35:41,281 --> 00:35:42,961
He couldn't bear to have it
in the house.

612
00:35:43,681 --> 00:35:46,001
"She's gone now, and that's
the end of it." That's what he said.

613
00:35:46,081 --> 00:35:47,841
Yeah. Funny old bloke, my dad.

614
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:51,801
Of course, now I realise
that was his way of dealing with it.

615
00:35:54,441 --> 00:35:57,761
When your mum died,
I had to go through all her stuff.

616
00:36:00,401 --> 00:36:01,481
But this is all mine.

617
00:36:02,041 --> 00:36:03,521
Yeah, I know. She kept it all.

618
00:36:10,081 --> 00:36:11,481
She once said to me, um,

619
00:36:12,881 --> 00:36:14,041
"If anyone

620
00:36:15,401 --> 00:36:17,521
"ever asks about me after I'm gone,

621
00:36:18,441 --> 00:36:19,681
"you tell them I was lucky.

622
00:36:21,761 --> 00:36:25,281
"Tell them I gave someone life
and I watched him grow

623
00:36:27,241 --> 00:36:28,241
"and I was proud.”

624
00:36:37,841 --> 00:36:38,921
Why didn't you come, Aaron?

625
00:36:40,281 --> 00:36:43,281
Not for you mum, or for Ryan,
but for yourself?

626
00:36:44,761 --> 00:36:45,921
I don't know.

627
00:36:53,081 --> 00:36:55,321
Maybe I thought if... (INHALES SHARPLY)

628
00:36:56,041 --> 00:36:57,921
I wasn't there, she wasn't gone.

629
00:37:06,201 --> 00:37:08,161
I wish I was better at life, Graham.

630
00:37:15,001 --> 00:37:17,521
Well, there's still time.

631
00:37:31,241 --> 00:37:32,361
Can I help you?

632
00:37:32,521 --> 00:37:33,801
What do you want? 'Cause I'm busy.

633
00:37:35,441 --> 00:37:37,081
The work will commence.

634
00:37:37,521 --> 00:37:38,521
What work?

635
00:37:38,801 --> 00:37:40,441
I shall be reborn.

636
00:37:41,441 --> 00:37:43,961
Humanity will be destroyed.

637
00:37:44,041 --> 00:37:46,361
All right, enough. Go on, off my farm.

638
00:37:46,641 --> 00:37:47,881
I don't care what you've been told,

639
00:37:47,961 --> 00:37:50,241
all that stuff's been paid for,
and I can prove it.

640
00:37:51,361 --> 00:37:53,481
You will be exterminated.

641
00:37:56,081 --> 00:37:57,601
(SCREAMING)

642
00:38:52,841 --> 00:38:53,921
(LIN PANTS)

643
00:38:54,041 --> 00:38:57,561
DALEK: No, do not stop.
Return to the work.

644
00:38:57,641 --> 00:39:00,921
You will obey.
The work must be completed.

645
00:39:01,201 --> 00:39:02,881
You are weakening.

646
00:39:03,361 --> 00:39:04,401
No.

647
00:39:04,481 --> 00:39:06,841
(INHALES SHARPLY) You are.

648
00:39:08,521 --> 00:39:09,561
(GRUNTS)

649
00:39:10,561 --> 00:39:13,201
You will stop this.
You cannot escape me.

650
00:39:13,281 --> 00:39:16,441
I will fight.

651
00:39:16,601 --> 00:39:18,961
-(GROANS)
-Stop!

652
00:39:20,881 --> 00:39:22,761
DOCTOR: Satellite signal's
tracked the car to here.

653
00:39:22,841 --> 00:39:24,281
So, Lin's here, eh?

654
00:39:24,641 --> 00:39:26,601
-Doctor.
-(PANTING)

655
00:39:31,721 --> 00:39:33,641
(BUZZING)

656
00:39:36,801 --> 00:39:38,761
That's all the signs of a Dalek weapon.

657
00:39:43,841 --> 00:39:45,281
That's what was at MDZ.

658
00:39:47,081 --> 00:39:48,961
It went and found it
after all this time.

659
00:39:49,881 --> 00:39:51,001
(THUD IN DISTANCE)

660
00:39:52,201 --> 00:39:54,441
-You don't have to come.
-RYAN: Of course, we do.

661
00:39:54,601 --> 00:39:55,841
We're always with you.

662
00:40:04,121 --> 00:40:05,401
LIN: Help.

663
00:40:05,481 --> 00:40:07,281
Listen. Can you hear that?

664
00:40:08,721 --> 00:40:10,121
-LIN: Help me.
-That's Lin.

665
00:40:14,041 --> 00:40:15,841
-(LIN GROANING)
-DOCTOR: I need to take a look at you.

666
00:40:15,921 --> 00:40:18,161
It's okay. I'm here. We're all here.

667
00:40:19,841 --> 00:40:21,481
Everything's all right, Lin.

668
00:40:22,641 --> 00:40:23,721
Is she gonna be okay?

669
00:40:24,001 --> 00:40:26,921
Whatever that thing secretes acted like
a plug on her neck once it left.

670
00:40:28,401 --> 00:40:29,441
Otherwise she'd be dead.

671
00:40:29,521 --> 00:40:31,121
(GROANING) I'm sorry.

672
00:40:31,961 --> 00:40:33,841
DOCTOR: You have
nothing to be sorry about.

673
00:40:34,121 --> 00:40:36,801
-You fought and you won.
-No, listen.

674
00:40:37,681 --> 00:40:38,921
It's still here.

675
00:40:53,161 --> 00:40:55,361
You three help her stand,
get her back to the TARDIS.

676
00:40:56,281 --> 00:40:58,281
There are supplies there
that'll help with the healing.

677
00:40:58,401 --> 00:40:59,401
What about you?

678
00:40:59,521 --> 00:41:00,761
I'm gonna find that creature.

679
00:41:00,841 --> 00:41:02,921
-You can't do that on your own.
-Always have done.

680
00:41:03,841 --> 00:41:05,961
Me and the Dalek, it's personal.

681
00:41:07,241 --> 00:41:08,361
Go on, get her safe.

682
00:41:08,881 --> 00:41:11,001
-Come on.
-(LIN PANTING)

683
00:41:45,841 --> 00:41:47,521
(GROWLING IN DISTANCE)

684
00:41:57,001 --> 00:41:58,481
(PANTING)

685
00:42:05,801 --> 00:42:07,521
Exterminate.

686
00:42:08,001 --> 00:42:10,401
DOCTOR: I'm blocking
your laser signals, mate.

687
00:42:10,881 --> 00:42:12,401
You're not fully in sync yet.

688
00:42:14,521 --> 00:42:15,881
So that's what you've been doing.

689
00:42:16,601 --> 00:42:18,561
Reconstructing yourself from memory.

690
00:42:19,721 --> 00:42:20,961
And remnants.

691
00:42:21,241 --> 00:42:23,841
And spare parts.

692
00:42:24,081 --> 00:42:25,881
I am rebuilt.

693
00:42:28,281 --> 00:42:29,281
What do you call this look?

694
00:42:29,641 --> 00:42:30,801
Junkyard chic?

695
00:42:31,161 --> 00:42:34,881
Earth is now under the control
of the Daleks.

696
00:42:35,121 --> 00:42:38,121
No, it's not.
You couldn't even control one person.

697
00:42:38,201 --> 00:42:40,361
Humanity will surrender.

698
00:42:40,841 --> 00:42:43,161
They really won't, trust me.
I've seen them in action.

699
00:42:43,681 --> 00:42:45,401
They've fought off so many things,

700
00:42:45,641 --> 00:42:47,801
including the worst of their own people.

701
00:42:49,161 --> 00:42:51,721
They're really stubborn.
Have you not worked that out yet?

702
00:42:53,001 --> 00:42:56,281
Even the recon scout Daleks,
the first ones out of Skaro.

703
00:42:56,481 --> 00:43:00,681
Humanity bands together, vanquishes you,
and buries you for centuries.

704
00:43:00,921 --> 00:43:02,881
Yet I survived.

705
00:43:03,401 --> 00:43:04,401
Yeah.

706
00:43:05,761 --> 00:43:06,761
You're good at that.

707
00:43:07,961 --> 00:43:09,201
It won't be enough.

708
00:43:09,801 --> 00:43:13,681
This planet is annexed.
The fleet will be summoned.

709
00:43:13,801 --> 00:43:16,681
You don't have the ability.
You don't have the strength.

710
00:43:16,881 --> 00:43:18,801
You are weak.

711
00:43:18,881 --> 00:43:20,681
Humanity is weak.

712
00:43:20,761 --> 00:43:23,321
Except I'm not human.

713
00:43:24,641 --> 00:43:25,641
Have a scan.

714
00:43:30,841 --> 00:43:33,561
Who are you? Identify.

715
00:43:34,201 --> 00:43:37,521
Oh, mate, I'm the Doctor.

716
00:43:37,881 --> 00:43:39,041
Ring any bells?

717
00:43:42,001 --> 00:43:45,601
-Sonic device override!
-I'll take that as a yes.

718
00:43:46,241 --> 00:43:50,521
The Doctor is an enemy
of all Daleks. Exterminate.

719
00:43:52,081 --> 00:43:53,881
(PANTING) Yes, I am.

720
00:43:53,961 --> 00:43:56,521
You want this planet,
you have to come through me.

721
00:43:56,841 --> 00:43:59,361
So why don't you make it easy
on yourself and leave now.

722
00:43:59,921 --> 00:44:02,201
Conquest has already started.

723
00:44:02,281 --> 00:44:05,801
-I have all the information I need.
-What information?

724
00:44:05,881 --> 00:44:08,001
Humanity will surrender.

725
00:44:08,081 --> 00:44:10,841
Dalek invasion fleet will be summoned.

726
00:44:10,921 --> 00:44:15,801
Total conquest of Earth
predicted in 9376 rels.

727
00:44:27,241 --> 00:44:28,361
(SIGHS)

728
00:44:28,721 --> 00:44:31,721
Now, I must remember. How long's a rel?

729
00:44:33,881 --> 00:44:36,041
-How'd it go? What happened?
-Did you get rid of it?

730
00:44:36,481 --> 00:44:38,521
-Not quite.
-How much "not quite"?

731
00:44:38,761 --> 00:44:41,041
Not at all. Slightly riled it,

732
00:44:41,441 --> 00:44:43,081
-and let it get away.
-RYAN: What?

733
00:44:43,201 --> 00:44:44,321
And now it's in a tank,

734
00:44:44,401 --> 00:44:46,321
-trying to summon the fleet.
-Doctor!

735
00:44:46,401 --> 00:44:48,201
All right, don't go on about it. I know.

736
00:44:48,761 --> 00:44:49,961
They're really persistent.

737
00:44:51,801 --> 00:44:53,161
Oh.

738
00:44:53,321 --> 00:44:55,881
-How you feeling, Lin?
-Uh, shaky.

739
00:44:55,961 --> 00:44:57,561
I'm not surprised. You will for a while.

740
00:44:57,681 --> 00:44:59,681
But you kept fighting it. Thank you.

741
00:44:59,961 --> 00:45:01,401
(CONSOLE WHIRS)

742
00:45:03,001 --> 00:45:04,721
Take these.
Three a minute for four minutes.

743
00:45:04,801 --> 00:45:06,841
Don't take with alcohol,
you'll grow an extra head.

744
00:45:07,601 --> 00:45:09,001
That was an embarrassing party.

745
00:45:12,081 --> 00:45:13,521
It was ready to kill me.

746
00:45:15,001 --> 00:45:19,601
I... I could feel its hatred
enveloping me. I...

747
00:45:20,641 --> 00:45:22,521
Is that what it's gonna do to the world?

748
00:45:22,641 --> 00:45:25,641
No. Because I'm gonna stop it.
We're gonna stop it.

749
00:45:26,001 --> 00:45:29,081
Somehow. Before humans
start engaging with it.

750
00:45:30,281 --> 00:45:31,921
It's flying
right through their airspace.

751
00:45:32,521 --> 00:45:33,561
Where's it going?

752
00:45:33,641 --> 00:45:34,881
(MOBILE RINGING)

753
00:45:36,841 --> 00:45:38,801
-What?
-Where are you?

754
00:45:38,881 --> 00:45:40,921
-In the TARDIS.
-You better be coming to pick me up.

755
00:45:41,001 --> 00:45:42,801
-Okay, fine.
-Right. Thank you.

756
00:45:43,681 --> 00:45:47,561
Um, Aaron, mate, little thing
we haven't told you.

757
00:45:47,681 --> 00:45:49,761
A tiny thing, so word of warning.

758
00:45:49,961 --> 00:45:51,481
You know that blue cabinet?

759
00:45:51,881 --> 00:45:53,561
That is just about to blow your mind.

760
00:45:53,761 --> 00:45:54,761
-What do you mean?
-(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

761
00:45:57,681 --> 00:45:58,961
GRAHAM: It travels,

762
00:46:00,321 --> 00:46:01,961
in space and time.

763
00:46:07,441 --> 00:46:08,481
Come on, quick.

764
00:46:08,641 --> 00:46:11,281
The Doc said you can come, too,
but Graham will have to explain.

765
00:46:27,761 --> 00:46:28,961
SOLDIER: Go! Go!

766
00:46:32,001 --> 00:46:33,121
Get back!

767
00:46:41,641 --> 00:46:43,081
Intercepted unknown drone.

768
00:46:43,561 --> 00:46:44,761
We have it surrounded.

769
00:46:45,561 --> 00:46:47,041
Surrender!

770
00:46:49,201 --> 00:46:50,361
Did it just talk?

771
00:46:50,521 --> 00:46:53,601
Allocated surrender period has expired.

772
00:46:53,681 --> 00:46:55,961
Consequence, extermination.

773
00:46:58,321 --> 00:46:59,921
Open fire!

774
00:47:06,601 --> 00:47:07,961
Cease fire!

775
00:47:10,881 --> 00:47:12,361
(WHIRRING)

776
00:47:17,201 --> 00:47:18,281
Run.

777
00:47:18,841 --> 00:47:22,041
-What?
-Run! That's an order!

778
00:47:22,361 --> 00:47:23,481
Go, go, go!

779
00:47:23,561 --> 00:47:27,841
The Dalek race is supreme.

780
00:47:56,641 --> 00:47:58,641
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

781
00:48:06,441 --> 00:48:07,561
Left.

782
00:48:16,281 --> 00:48:17,561
SOLDIER: Out! Out!

783
00:48:23,041 --> 00:48:24,881
DOCTOR: Oh, new heat signal.

784
00:48:24,961 --> 00:48:27,441
And a non-terrestrial form
moving away from it fast.

785
00:48:28,241 --> 00:48:31,761
I'm on its tail. Sorry, the TARDIS
isn't designed for these short hops.

786
00:48:31,841 --> 00:48:33,281
(DOCTOR GRUNTS)

787
00:48:33,801 --> 00:48:36,241
Ah, a microwave.

788
00:48:36,641 --> 00:48:38,081
Who brought a microwave with them?

789
00:48:38,201 --> 00:48:40,561
It's actually an oven and a microwave.

790
00:48:41,281 --> 00:48:42,361
Nice.

791
00:48:42,681 --> 00:48:44,281
What is this place?

792
00:48:45,481 --> 00:48:47,041
This is where I've been since Nan died.

793
00:48:47,521 --> 00:48:49,081
Travelling the universe with these guys.

794
00:48:49,161 --> 00:48:51,641
Even if we track this Dalek thing,
how do we stop it?

795
00:48:51,761 --> 00:48:54,281
-I'm still working on that.
-The Custodians managed it.

796
00:48:54,521 --> 00:48:56,281
If we take the same approach
as those drawings...

797
00:48:56,361 --> 00:48:57,881
Those documents aren't reliable, Mitch.

798
00:48:57,961 --> 00:49:00,041
Yeah, except all the rumours
have proved to be true.

799
00:49:00,121 --> 00:49:01,161
It's shown here.

800
00:49:02,241 --> 00:49:04,641
Short version,
alien psychopath in its own tank

801
00:49:04,721 --> 00:49:06,001
trying to bring loads more to Earth.

802
00:49:06,241 --> 00:49:07,881
I guess this is how they attacked it
last time.

803
00:49:07,961 --> 00:49:10,241
-What's it made of?
-Remnants of its original shell.

804
00:49:10,361 --> 00:49:12,921
Patched up with
all sorts of spare parts, mainly metal.

805
00:49:13,201 --> 00:49:15,241
-You can use my oven.
-It's not gonna fit in there.

806
00:49:15,481 --> 00:49:18,281
That's not what I meant.
Help me break it up.

807
00:49:18,601 --> 00:49:21,081
(CONSOLE BEEPING)

808
00:49:24,641 --> 00:49:26,801
DOCTOR: That Dalek's moving fast,
but where's it going?

809
00:49:27,481 --> 00:49:28,961
AARON: Ryan,
help me get the element out.

810
00:49:29,041 --> 00:49:30,881
RYAN: Why?
AARON: It's metal.

811
00:49:31,081 --> 00:49:32,761
Oh, you're good, Ryan's dad.

812
00:49:33,161 --> 00:49:35,041
You're almost making up
for your parenting deficit.

813
00:49:35,401 --> 00:49:36,681
(CONSOLE BEEPING)

814
00:49:38,561 --> 00:49:39,801
I know where it's heading.

815
00:49:40,321 --> 00:49:42,841
The biggest communications resource
in the country.

816
00:49:58,481 --> 00:50:00,601
-(EXPLOSIONS IN DISTANCE)
-(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

817
00:50:19,161 --> 00:50:21,441
I don't mean you any harm.

818
00:50:21,641 --> 00:50:23,481
Exterminate.

819
00:50:25,681 --> 00:50:28,721
Communication headquarters acquired.

820
00:50:28,801 --> 00:50:31,841
Aligning all signals to Dalek fleet.

821
00:50:32,161 --> 00:50:36,921
All power will be diverted
towards fleet signal transmission.

822
00:50:44,161 --> 00:50:46,321
Earth is annexed.

823
00:50:46,401 --> 00:50:49,681
It's diverting every bit of power
it can take from the whole of the UK

824
00:50:50,041 --> 00:50:51,401
to power the transmission.

825
00:50:53,881 --> 00:50:55,321
It's shutting down the Wi-Fi.

826
00:50:55,681 --> 00:50:57,361
-The phone signals.
-(TARDIS BEEPING)

827
00:50:58,561 --> 00:51:01,761
Whoa! That Dalek just shut down
the whole of Britain's Internet.

828
00:51:02,481 --> 00:51:03,961
What, on New Year's Day?

829
00:51:04,041 --> 00:51:06,161
When everything's shut
and everyone's hung over?

830
00:51:07,361 --> 00:51:08,401
What a monster.

831
00:51:08,801 --> 00:51:10,201
(KEYS CLACKING)

832
00:51:11,361 --> 00:51:12,521
The Wi-Fi's gone off.

833
00:51:13,481 --> 00:51:17,201
Everything's gone off. No Wi-Fi,
no phone signal. It's all down.

834
00:51:17,441 --> 00:51:18,561
Not even Netflix?

835
00:51:19,161 --> 00:51:20,561
(REMOTE KEYS CLICKING)

836
00:51:20,841 --> 00:51:22,841
-Nothing.
-What do we do?

837
00:51:24,601 --> 00:51:25,641
I suppose

838
00:51:26,921 --> 00:51:28,961
we'll have to have a conversation?

839
00:51:30,761 --> 00:51:31,881
BOTH: What?

840
00:51:32,761 --> 00:51:34,561
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

841
00:51:42,001 --> 00:51:44,321
-Don't shoot.
-Exterminate!

842
00:51:48,161 --> 00:51:50,681
Do you think I'm daft enough
to stand here without shields?

843
00:51:51,441 --> 00:51:52,721
It's safe, gang.

844
00:51:53,761 --> 00:51:56,361
DALEK: Hide behind your shields, Doctor.

845
00:51:56,441 --> 00:52:00,081
You and your human friends,
you have failed.

846
00:52:00,201 --> 00:52:01,641
Say hello to a Dalek.

847
00:52:01,801 --> 00:52:04,961
Signal activation in nine rels.

848
00:52:05,161 --> 00:52:07,801
-The fleet shall be summoned.
-No, it won't.

849
00:52:08,321 --> 00:52:11,681
No matter how many times you try,
no matter how long you wait,

850
00:52:11,881 --> 00:52:13,361
I will always be in your way.

851
00:52:13,441 --> 00:52:15,441
Backed up by the best of humanity.

852
00:52:15,521 --> 00:52:19,201
Now, final, final, final warning.

853
00:52:19,521 --> 00:52:21,921
'Cause I'm nice.
I really do try my best.

854
00:52:22,881 --> 00:52:25,361
Stop the signal, get off this planet.

855
00:52:26,201 --> 00:52:28,961
You are not my commander.

856
00:52:30,601 --> 00:52:33,881
I tried. You heard me, right?
I tried, I gave it a chance.

857
00:52:34,281 --> 00:52:35,681
-Yep, yep.
-You did, you did.

858
00:52:35,881 --> 00:52:38,121
I'm fast enough, right?
I'm fast enough for this plan?

859
00:52:39,201 --> 00:52:40,521
-Uh, probably.
-Maybe.

860
00:52:40,601 --> 00:52:42,321
-Possibly.
-Well, that one needs work.

861
00:52:44,241 --> 00:52:46,201
Here's a New Year message
for you to send.

862
00:52:46,321 --> 00:52:50,561
Earth is protected by me and my mates.
This year and every other.

863
00:52:51,081 --> 00:52:52,081
Here we go!

864
00:52:58,841 --> 00:53:00,601
DALEK: Exterminate the Doctor.

865
00:53:00,841 --> 00:53:03,521
The Doctor must be exterminated.

866
00:53:04,521 --> 00:53:05,601
DOCTOR: Now, gang!

867
00:53:06,041 --> 00:53:08,761
-GRAHAM: Come on, Doc.
-None of you will survive.

868
00:53:09,081 --> 00:53:10,401
DOCTOR: Aim for one of the servers.

869
00:53:11,081 --> 00:53:13,761
...weaponry malfunctioning.

870
00:53:13,841 --> 00:53:15,481
DOCTOR: No, attach the parts.
-Weapon failure!

871
00:53:15,561 --> 00:53:17,321
The parts are on, Doctor. Get clear!

872
00:53:17,801 --> 00:53:19,561
Working on my casing.

873
00:53:19,921 --> 00:53:21,601
The Custodians burned your shell.

874
00:53:21,681 --> 00:53:23,281
And we've got something
they didn't have.

875
00:53:23,361 --> 00:53:26,841
A nicely-designed, portable
combination oven. Transformers,

876
00:53:27,321 --> 00:53:29,201
primary and secondary coils,

877
00:53:29,321 --> 00:53:30,961
going from high voltage, low am page,

878
00:53:31,041 --> 00:53:33,441
to low voltage, very, very high am page.

879
00:53:33,881 --> 00:53:35,241
(WHIRRING LOUDLY)

880
00:53:36,641 --> 00:53:38,521
-Get down!
-(DALEK SCREAMING)

881
00:53:39,561 --> 00:53:41,241
(WHIRRING STOPS)

882
00:53:47,321 --> 00:53:48,521
RYAN: Is it dead?

883
00:53:49,121 --> 00:53:51,761
-(PANTING)
-(BUZZING)

884
00:53:54,881 --> 00:53:56,001
Signal never sent.

885
00:53:57,001 --> 00:53:59,161
I think that was my best skid ever.

886
00:53:59,401 --> 00:54:00,441
I'm so chuffed.

887
00:54:00,641 --> 00:54:01,761
Well done, team.

888
00:54:01,961 --> 00:54:04,321
Gang. Extended fam.

889
00:54:05,001 --> 00:54:07,601
(DALEK LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

890
00:54:11,121 --> 00:54:12,121
RYAN: Dad...

891
00:54:14,201 --> 00:54:16,401
You underestimate me,

892
00:54:17,881 --> 00:54:19,601
Doctor.

893
00:54:20,561 --> 00:54:22,361
Dalek survives.

894
00:54:22,561 --> 00:54:23,801
Doctor, do something.

895
00:54:24,681 --> 00:54:25,881
I'm sorry, Aaron,

896
00:54:27,161 --> 00:54:28,281
I miscalculated.

897
00:54:28,801 --> 00:54:31,841
You'll take me to the Dalek fleet.

898
00:54:33,881 --> 00:54:36,321
-Resist...
-(GROANS)

899
00:54:38,281 --> 00:54:41,841
-...and this body will be destroyed.
-RYAN: Doctor, do something.

900
00:54:43,841 --> 00:54:44,881
Fine.

901
00:54:45,561 --> 00:54:47,041
Doctor, seriously.

902
00:54:47,361 --> 00:54:48,481
My decision.

903
00:54:50,041 --> 00:54:52,441
Whatever you want.
Just promise me you'll let him go.

904
00:54:57,081 --> 00:54:59,481
You are my prisoners now.

905
00:55:05,481 --> 00:55:10,161
The glory of the TARDIS shall be ours.

906
00:55:11,521 --> 00:55:13,121
-Help him.
-Trust me.

907
00:55:17,721 --> 00:55:18,721
We've landed.

908
00:55:18,801 --> 00:55:22,001
Finally, my mission is complete.

909
00:55:23,201 --> 00:55:26,561
The Earth and the Doctor shall submit

910
00:55:27,081 --> 00:55:29,201
before the Dalek fleet.

911
00:55:31,681 --> 00:55:32,721
(SCREAMS)

912
00:55:32,801 --> 00:55:34,361
RYAN: Doctor! What are you doing?

913
00:55:37,641 --> 00:55:39,001
DOCTOR: Sorry, did I not mention?

914
00:55:39,601 --> 00:55:43,241
No fleet. Only a sun going supernova.

915
00:55:43,681 --> 00:55:46,921
And a squid-sized vacuum corridor

916
00:55:47,001 --> 00:55:49,561
-about to pull you out into space.
-Dad!

917
00:55:49,761 --> 00:55:52,401
You're too weak, Dalek.
You can't hold on.

918
00:55:52,601 --> 00:55:54,881
Except it is holding on, Doctor.

919
00:55:55,401 --> 00:55:56,401
All right.

920
00:55:57,481 --> 00:56:00,881
Argh! The vacuum corridor's expanding,
I can't control it.

921
00:56:01,201 --> 00:56:04,001
-GRAHAM: What do you mean?
-It's gonna take Aaron with it.

922
00:56:04,761 --> 00:56:05,841
(DOCTOR EXCLAIMS)

923
00:56:06,041 --> 00:56:07,721
Everybody, hold on!

924
00:56:08,721 --> 00:56:10,681
(ALL SHOUTING)

925
00:56:18,161 --> 00:56:20,241
Dad! Doctor, help him.

926
00:56:20,681 --> 00:56:22,721
(GRUNTING)

927
00:56:24,081 --> 00:56:25,521
No, Dad! Hold on!

928
00:56:25,601 --> 00:56:26,721
Ryan!

929
00:56:29,681 --> 00:56:32,561
(PANTING) Dad.
Dad, I know you can hear me.

930
00:56:33,161 --> 00:56:35,041
(GROWLS)

931
00:56:35,721 --> 00:56:38,201
He is mine now!

932
00:56:38,281 --> 00:56:40,641
No, he's not! He's mine.

933
00:56:40,921 --> 00:56:42,041
(GASPING)

934
00:56:42,921 --> 00:56:45,161
Dad. Dad, I'm here for you.

935
00:56:47,721 --> 00:56:49,121
I forgive you.

936
00:56:51,921 --> 00:56:53,121
I love you, Dad.

937
00:56:56,481 --> 00:56:57,481
Take my hand.

938
00:56:58,041 --> 00:56:59,041
Fight it!

939
00:56:59,361 --> 00:57:00,401
Take my hand!

940
00:57:09,361 --> 00:57:10,601
(RYAN GRUNTS)

941
00:57:10,801 --> 00:57:12,601
Leave my dad alone!

942
00:57:13,241 --> 00:57:15,041
(DALEK SCREAMING)

943
00:57:21,721 --> 00:57:22,721
(BOTH GRUNT)

944
00:57:22,801 --> 00:57:24,121
(PANTING)

945
00:57:30,441 --> 00:57:32,801
(GROANS) I've got you.

946
00:57:32,881 --> 00:57:33,961
(PANTING)

947
00:57:34,801 --> 00:57:36,681
Not bad for a kid with dyspraxia, right?

948
00:57:37,241 --> 00:57:38,281
Not bad at all.

949
00:57:57,041 --> 00:57:58,641
DOCTOR: Think that's everything
back in place.

950
00:57:58,801 --> 00:58:01,681
Next time, you go looking for
anything that goes missing.

951
00:58:02,881 --> 00:58:04,081
You're really going in that?

952
00:58:04,521 --> 00:58:06,121
This is what you do?

953
00:58:06,481 --> 00:58:07,801
Yeah. You fancy a trip?

954
00:58:10,121 --> 00:58:11,401
(LAUGHS) No.

955
00:58:13,881 --> 00:58:15,161
Call me when you get back.

956
00:58:15,721 --> 00:58:18,241
-You are coming back?
-Yeah, of course.

957
00:58:19,881 --> 00:58:21,801
-Look after him.
-Always.

958
00:58:32,601 --> 00:58:34,761
DOCTOR: Come on then, you lot.
Places to go.

959
00:58:36,161 --> 00:58:39,401
YASMIN: When you say "places to go,"
what are you thinking?

960
00:58:39,721 --> 00:58:41,001
Where to next?

961
00:58:42,201 --> 00:58:43,241
I was thinking...

962
00:58:47,081 --> 00:58:48,161
Everywhere.

963
00:58:52,161 --> 00:58:55,401
NARRATOR:
On the first day of the year 20189,

964
00:58:55,921 --> 00:58:58,161
across the land and sky of Britain,

965
00:58:58,761 --> 00:59:01,121
an army of unlikely friends
came together

966
00:59:01,201 --> 00:59:03,161
to face an impossible opponent,

967
00:59:04,401 --> 00:59:05,561
and prevailed.

968
00:59:12,001 --> 00:59:14,281
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

